1
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:14,880
(South City
Chinese and Western Medicine Clinic)

2
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:24,560
(South City
Chinese and Western Medicine Clinic)

3
00:00:28,740 --> 00:00:31,719
(South City
Chinese and Western Medicine Clinic)

4
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:35,720
=Cases Between Us=

5
00:00:35,960 --> 00:00:39,120
=Episode 27=

6
00:00:41,780 --> 00:00:43,179
Ge Fan did commit murder

7
00:00:43,180 --> 00:00:44,500
and is guilty under the law.

8
00:00:44,740 --> 00:00:47,350
But if Dr. Cheng hadn't favored Tao Zhi,

9
00:00:47,350 --> 00:00:49,140
she never would've
stood by and watched him die.

10
00:00:49,140 --> 00:00:51,859
If she hadn't, Zhang Cong would've had
nothing to blackmail her with.

11
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:53,140
And she wouldn't have ended up

12
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:55,970
going down this path.

13
00:00:56,330 --> 00:00:57,690
Trading a life

14
00:00:57,860 --> 00:01:00,140
for the chance
to practice medicine fairly.

15
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:01,249
When has this world

16
00:01:01,250 --> 00:01:03,460
ever been kind to women?

17
00:01:04,130 --> 00:01:05,609
Xie Fu came north to pursue her dream,

18
00:01:05,610 --> 00:01:07,489
only to be sold into
the Eight Alleys for no reason

19
00:01:07,490 --> 00:01:08,780
and die there.

20
00:01:09,490 --> 00:01:10,650
And my sister too.

21
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:11,769
Ever since her divorce,

22
00:01:11,770 --> 00:01:12,739
the gossip in this city

23
00:01:12,740 --> 00:01:14,029
has been enough to drown her.

24
00:01:14,029 --> 00:01:15,179
Good thing she's got a temper.

25
00:01:15,179 --> 00:01:17,220
Anyone badmouths her,
she slaps them on the spot.

26
00:01:17,660 --> 00:01:19,700
Anyone else would've
been driven to hang herself.

27
00:01:21,460 --> 00:01:23,220
I just hope that one day,

28
00:01:24,280 --> 00:01:26,500
women won't have to risk their lives

29
00:01:26,940 --> 00:01:29,620
just to walk their own path with dignity.

30
00:01:34,770 --> 00:01:35,730
What?

31
00:01:37,460 --> 00:01:38,700
Never thought

32
00:01:38,820 --> 00:01:41,249
I'd see the day when the righteous,

33
00:01:41,250 --> 00:01:43,049
stubborn Chief Yuan

34
00:01:43,050 --> 00:01:45,579
finally understood

35
00:01:45,580 --> 00:01:46,730
how the real world works.

36
00:01:47,210 --> 00:01:48,129
I'm truly touched.

37
00:01:48,130 --> 00:01:50,730
Looks like these past few days
haven't been wasted following me around.

38
00:01:55,130 --> 00:01:56,370
Who's following you?

39
00:01:56,580 --> 00:01:58,730
You're the one always
tagging along with me.

40
00:01:58,740 --> 00:02:00,060
Alright, alright.

41
00:02:02,250 --> 00:02:03,459
Back to business.

42
00:02:03,460 --> 00:02:04,869
Did Du Wenjiu test the Strength Pills?

43
00:02:04,869 --> 00:02:06,559
It's been days,
and we still haven't heard anything.

44
00:02:06,559 --> 00:02:08,929
Relax. Who knows
what he's been busy with lately?

45
00:02:08,930 --> 00:02:11,650
If he's neglecting his duties,
take it up with him. Don't blame me.

46
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:15,900
How are you such an overbearing chief?

47
00:02:43,530 --> 00:02:44,530
Dr. Du.

48
00:02:46,650 --> 00:02:47,580
Dr. Du.

49
00:02:47,930 --> 00:02:49,489
The test you asked for

50
00:02:49,490 --> 00:02:50,690
is back.

51
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:56,620
Methamphetamine.

52
00:02:57,930 --> 00:02:58,649
Zhang Cong said

53
00:02:58,650 --> 00:03:00,259
you were the one
who added methamphetamine

54
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:01,620
to the Strength Pills.

55
00:03:01,860 --> 00:03:02,780
I did.

56
00:03:02,980 --> 00:03:04,180
Where did you get it?

57
00:03:04,810 --> 00:03:06,859
A nurse gave it to me.

58
00:03:06,860 --> 00:03:08,620
She said it helps keep one alert.

59
00:03:09,420 --> 00:03:10,740
Where is she now?

60
00:03:13,580 --> 00:03:15,620
She died in a car accident last month.

61
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:22,020
Which clinic did she work at?

62
00:03:22,050 --> 00:03:24,060
It's a clinic run by a Japanese.

63
00:03:24,770 --> 00:03:27,250
I never asked which one.

64
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,859
(Serene and Patience)

65
00:03:32,860 --> 00:03:33,690
Alright.

66
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:37,340
Mr. Zhao.

67
00:03:43,420 --> 00:03:46,340
Are you close with Douding?

68
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:49,089
We're acquainted.

69
00:03:49,090 --> 00:03:50,780
I still have some savings.

70
00:03:51,210 --> 00:03:52,460
I won't be needing them

71
00:03:52,490 --> 00:03:53,780
anymore.

72
00:03:54,530 --> 00:03:57,220
Could you send her to school?

73
00:03:58,370 --> 00:03:59,410
Uh,

74
00:04:00,530 --> 00:04:02,090
are you related?

75
00:04:04,420 --> 00:04:05,810
She's an orphan.

76
00:04:06,210 --> 00:04:08,130
I'm not even that close to her.

77
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:09,579
I just once overheard

78
00:04:09,580 --> 00:04:11,460
her arguing with Zhang Cong.

79
00:04:11,860 --> 00:04:13,410
She wanted to go to school.

80
00:04:16,020 --> 00:04:17,340
Why help her?

81
00:04:21,940 --> 00:04:23,580
Because in a world like this,

82
00:04:24,330 --> 00:04:26,220
for a girl with no family or connections,

83
00:04:26,260 --> 00:04:27,820
it's too hard

84
00:04:29,170 --> 00:04:30,410
to make something of herself.

85
00:04:53,970 --> 00:04:54,820
Alright.

86
00:04:56,090 --> 00:04:56,970
I'm off.

87
00:05:20,380 --> 00:05:22,139
Douding's settled in at school.

88
00:05:22,140 --> 00:05:24,090
Meanwhile, you're hiding out here.

89
00:05:27,500 --> 00:05:27,849
Why

90
00:05:27,850 --> 00:05:29,780
didn't you come with me today?

91
00:05:31,650 --> 00:05:33,580
Doing good deeds

92
00:05:34,090 --> 00:05:35,340
doesn't suit my image.

93
00:05:36,290 --> 00:05:37,460
Oh, come on.

94
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:39,380
Aren't you usually the biggest show-off?

95
00:05:42,290 --> 00:05:44,479
I can show off all I want, but a little girl

96
00:05:44,479 --> 00:05:46,649
clings to your sleeve in tears
on her first day of school,

97
00:05:46,650 --> 00:05:47,970
who can handle that?

98
00:05:48,650 --> 00:05:50,649
Everyone knows I'm a soft touch.

99
00:05:50,650 --> 00:05:51,939
If I cry on the street,

100
00:05:51,940 --> 00:05:54,460
where would the reputation
of Jingshi's number one dandy go?

101
00:05:55,580 --> 00:05:56,970
So you sent me instead?

102
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:00,729
Aren't you well-known
for being cold-hearted?

103
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:02,440
You're the most merciful goddess in Jingshi.

104
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:03,530
Merciful goddess.

105
00:06:05,090 --> 00:06:06,820
Now that's more like it.

106
00:06:07,940 --> 00:06:09,820
You had me worried there.

107
00:06:28,380 --> 00:06:30,410
Why are you so angry?

108
00:06:30,850 --> 00:06:31,769
Following Ge Fan's lead,

109
00:06:31,770 --> 00:06:33,289
we searched the Japanese clinic.

110
00:06:33,290 --> 00:06:35,819
We searched high and low,
but there was no methamphetamine.

111
00:06:35,820 --> 00:06:37,409
Neither the doctor nor the nurse

112
00:06:37,410 --> 00:06:38,730
said a word.

113
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:41,769
Alright.

114
00:06:41,770 --> 00:06:42,970
Calm down.

115
00:06:43,460 --> 00:06:45,650
(Invitation)
A kind citizen has come bearing gifts.

116
00:06:45,970 --> 00:06:47,220
Not interested.

117
00:06:47,290 --> 00:06:49,220
You're turning it down
without even looking?

118
00:06:49,260 --> 00:06:50,970
Do you think I have time for this?

119
00:06:51,210 --> 00:06:51,499
What?

120
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:53,019
You think all I ever do is have fun?

121
00:06:53,020 --> 00:06:54,700
Take a look at it. Read it.

122
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,540
(You are cordially invited
to a gathering at my residence.)

123
00:06:56,540 --> 00:06:57,560
(With regards, Masashige Kobayashi)

124
00:06:57,970 --> 00:06:59,090
Masashige Kobayashi?

125
00:06:59,170 --> 00:07:01,260
Director Li was transferred to Customs.

126
00:07:01,290 --> 00:07:02,329
I asked him to look into it.

127
00:07:02,330 --> 00:07:04,019
Everything supplied to Yamamoto Clinic

128
00:07:04,020 --> 00:07:05,849
came from Masashige Kobayashi.

129
00:07:05,850 --> 00:07:08,580
He's hosting a gathering tonight.
Why don't we go and have a look?

130
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:09,819
How did you get this?

131
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:11,289
Don't worry about that.

132
00:07:11,290 --> 00:07:13,019
Just make sure you're dressed nicely

133
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:13,769
for the occasion.

134
00:07:13,770 --> 00:07:15,610
Don't get stopped at the door.

135
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:17,700
Just worry about yourself.

136
00:07:35,170 --> 00:07:37,529
I traded three afternoon teas
with the Japanese ambassador's daughter

137
00:07:37,530 --> 00:07:39,580
for this invitation.

138
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:41,939
My waist's an inch bigger now.

139
00:07:41,940 --> 00:07:43,290
Just remember,

140
00:07:43,850 --> 00:07:45,289
whatever you find tonight,

141
00:07:45,290 --> 00:07:47,059
I get the exclusive.

142
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:48,290
Don't worry, Miss Zhao.

143
00:07:48,410 --> 00:07:49,940
We got it.

144
00:07:56,290 --> 00:07:57,380
Thank you all for coming.

145
00:07:58,700 --> 00:07:59,850
Thank you for coming.

146
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,969
(Masashige Kobayashi)

147
00:08:01,970 --> 00:08:04,490
Thank you all for coming.

148
00:08:05,580 --> 00:08:07,000
Masashige Kobayashi?

149
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,999
He's been away from Beijing for quite some time
and only returned the day before yesterday.

150
00:08:09,999 --> 00:08:11,729
Tonight's banquet
is to welcome him back.

151
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:13,059
Thank you all

152
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,729
for attending my banquet.

153
00:08:14,730 --> 00:08:17,220
Please enjoy yourselves.

154
00:08:18,330 --> 00:08:19,940
Masashige Kobayashi!

155
00:08:21,060 --> 00:08:22,059
Mr. Xu.

156
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:23,490
Long time no see.

157
00:08:26,580 --> 00:08:28,380
You've got some nerve to come back here.

158
00:08:29,260 --> 00:08:30,220
You!

159
00:08:30,620 --> 00:08:31,900
Let go!

160
00:08:32,690 --> 00:08:33,770
Mr. Xu,

161
00:08:34,690 --> 00:08:36,289
what was that supposed to mean?

162
00:08:36,290 --> 00:08:38,010
China is a friendly nation.

163
00:08:38,020 --> 00:08:39,449
Why shouldn't I return?

164
00:08:39,450 --> 00:08:41,130
You know perfectly well.

165
00:08:41,650 --> 00:08:44,340
Your so-called health drinks

166
00:08:44,570 --> 00:08:46,649
are nothing but poison.

167
00:08:46,650 --> 00:08:48,339
They've killed countless innocent people.

168
00:08:48,340 --> 00:08:49,580
Shut it.

169
00:08:50,020 --> 00:08:51,060
Mr. Xu,

170
00:08:51,220 --> 00:08:53,300
watch your tongue.

171
00:08:53,570 --> 00:08:56,649
Those are baseless accusations.

172
00:08:56,650 --> 00:08:57,409
My Fourth Madam

173
00:08:57,410 --> 00:09:00,019
drank one of your health drinks.

174
00:09:00,020 --> 00:09:02,859
Her teeth and hair fell out.
Her bones ached unbearably.

175
00:09:02,860 --> 00:09:04,580
In the end, she died.

176
00:09:04,860 --> 00:09:05,619
After it happened,

177
00:09:05,620 --> 00:09:07,289
you ran back to Japan.

178
00:09:07,290 --> 00:09:08,970
Don't those symptoms

179
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:10,820
sound like what happened to your mother?

180
00:09:11,570 --> 00:09:13,219
Kobayashi, listen well.

181
00:09:13,220 --> 00:09:14,970
Even if I lose

182
00:09:15,220 --> 00:09:17,970
this position,

183
00:09:17,980 --> 00:09:19,979
I'll expose the true face

184
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:22,250
of you Japanese devils!

185
00:09:29,620 --> 00:09:31,219
You've all heard him.

186
00:09:31,220 --> 00:09:33,940
Our health drink
sells extremely well in Japan.

187
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:37,970
How did it become poison
when it reached China?

188
00:09:42,570 --> 00:09:43,660
Mr. Xu,

189
00:09:44,340 --> 00:09:47,490
I understand your grief.

190
00:09:47,770 --> 00:09:49,619
But if you make reckless accusations

191
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:51,569
and damage the friendship
between our two nations,

192
00:09:51,570 --> 00:09:54,139
can you bear the consequences?

193
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:54,529
You!

194
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:55,660
Don't forget.

195
00:09:56,530 --> 00:09:58,529
If something gets out of hand,

196
00:09:58,530 --> 00:10:00,250
it won't end well for anyone.

197
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:05,409
I'm sure

198
00:10:05,410 --> 00:10:07,890
you're a sensible man, Secretary Xu.

199
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:13,339
It seems you've been overworked lately.

200
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:16,300
Also, after drinking
my fine wine tonight,

201
00:10:16,450 --> 00:10:17,970
he lost his composure.

202
00:10:18,450 --> 00:10:21,130
Please escort Secretary Xu home
so he can get some rest.

203
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:23,569
Don't touch me with your filthy hands!

204
00:10:23,570 --> 00:10:24,940
Get off me!

205
00:10:29,650 --> 00:10:31,970
You'll get what's coming to you.

206
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:47,090
It's just a misunderstanding.

207
00:10:47,450 --> 00:10:48,700
It's just a misunderstanding.

208
00:10:48,740 --> 00:10:50,809
Sorry to spoil your evening.

209
00:10:50,810 --> 00:10:51,999
Please forgive me.

210
00:10:52,240 --> 00:11:10,040
(Pine Breeze Lodge)

211
00:11:10,260 --> 00:11:12,180
Isn't he Masashige Kobayashi's bodyguard?

212
00:11:28,650 --> 00:11:30,730
Secretary Xu lives in the city.

213
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:32,370
Why are they heading out to the suburbs?

214
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:34,929
Doesn't something feel off?

215
00:11:34,930 --> 00:11:37,060
Would a sly fox like Secretary Xu

216
00:11:37,260 --> 00:11:39,029
be stupid enough

217
00:11:39,030 --> 00:11:40,700
to make a scene at a Japanese banquet?

218
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:44,700
Secretary Xu's Fourth Madam
died from the same symptoms as your mother.

219
00:11:45,140 --> 00:11:47,580
Do you think Kobayashi gave your father
that drink too?

220
00:12:02,700 --> 00:12:03,999
- He mustn't die!
- He mustn't die!

221
00:12:10,140 --> 00:12:11,090
Get out.

222
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:55,339
What's in that drink?

223
00:12:55,340 --> 00:12:56,859
Why are they so desperate to silence you?

224
00:12:56,860 --> 00:12:57,499
Chief Yuan,

225
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,700
I'm reporting a murder.

226
00:12:58,810 --> 00:13:01,060
The Japanese poisoned someone.

227
00:13:07,690 --> 00:13:08,859
Count your blessings.

228
00:13:08,860 --> 00:13:11,139
- Easy, easy.
- The artery is right next to the wound.

229
00:13:11,140 --> 00:13:11,569
Be gentle.

230
00:13:11,570 --> 00:13:12,499
If you hit the artery,

231
00:13:12,500 --> 00:13:13,929
even the immortals couldn't save you.

232
00:13:13,930 --> 00:13:15,610
It's bleeding through.

233
00:13:19,050 --> 00:13:20,409
Don't listen to his nonsense.

234
00:13:20,410 --> 00:13:21,730
What a jinx.

235
00:13:23,050 --> 00:13:24,060
Tell me.

236
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,460
How did this happen?

237
00:13:33,740 --> 00:13:36,060
Did you two get into a mess
because of this drink?

238
00:13:36,100 --> 00:13:38,490
Someone was poisoned and died
after drinking it.

239
00:13:38,530 --> 00:13:39,689
What were the symptoms?

240
00:13:39,690 --> 00:13:41,619
Hair loss, teeth falling out,

241
00:13:41,620 --> 00:13:43,010
severe bone pain.

242
00:14:00,050 --> 00:14:01,979
Loose teeth. Hair loss.

243
00:14:01,980 --> 00:14:03,049
Bone necrosis.

244
00:14:03,050 --> 00:14:04,660
And kidney failure.

245
00:14:05,980 --> 00:14:07,370
Could it be a radium drink?

246
00:14:07,650 --> 00:14:08,610
Radium?

247
00:14:08,980 --> 00:14:09,979
The element

248
00:14:09,980 --> 00:14:11,449
discovered by Marie Curie?

249
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:12,300
Yes.

250
00:14:12,650 --> 00:14:13,929
I've heard of it.

251
00:14:13,930 --> 00:14:16,169
A couple of years ago,
doctors across Europe

252
00:14:16,170 --> 00:14:17,529
were using it to treat tumors.

253
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:18,649
The results were remarkable.

254
00:14:18,650 --> 00:14:19,859
But now,

255
00:14:19,860 --> 00:14:20,899
many people have died

256
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:22,529
from organ failure

257
00:14:22,530 --> 00:14:24,259
after drinking radium tonics
for a long time.

258
00:14:24,260 --> 00:14:25,809
This is the latest research.

259
00:14:25,810 --> 00:14:27,940
It says radium may cause
a form of radiation sickness.

260
00:14:29,260 --> 00:14:30,770
The symptoms match what you described.

261
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:33,920
(Bleeding gums, back pain,
and multiple organ failure)

262
00:14:37,930 --> 00:14:39,800
How soon can you tell
whether the drink contains radium?

263
00:14:39,800 --> 00:14:40,859
Radium isn't a compound.

264
00:14:40,860 --> 00:14:42,289
We can't test for it here.

265
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:43,970
I'll send it out for testing immediately.

266
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:52,730
Bye.

267
00:14:55,380 --> 00:14:56,180
Let's go.

268
00:15:02,100 --> 00:15:03,300
You go ahead.

269
00:15:04,900 --> 00:15:06,010
You're not going home?

270
00:15:07,170 --> 00:15:09,540
If my father sees me like this,

271
00:15:10,140 --> 00:15:11,619
he'll lock me in the house.

272
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:13,660
Then who'll keep Jingshi safe?

273
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:14,929
So?

274
00:15:14,930 --> 00:15:15,979
So,

275
00:15:15,980 --> 00:15:17,409
could you take me in for a few days?

276
00:15:17,410 --> 00:15:19,340
I'll leave once I'm healed.

277
00:15:22,220 --> 00:15:25,090
It's for the good people of Jingshi too.

278
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:35,820
Xiaoyuan,

279
00:15:36,930 --> 00:15:39,010
don't you get lonely

280
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:41,940
living here all by yourself?

281
00:15:42,770 --> 00:15:43,820
No.

282
00:15:44,900 --> 00:15:45,649
Who asked you?

283
00:15:45,650 --> 00:15:46,739
I was asking the dog.

284
00:15:46,740 --> 00:15:47,660
Right?

285
00:15:49,340 --> 00:15:50,259
Don't make up names.

286
00:15:50,260 --> 00:15:51,499
He already has one.

287
00:15:51,500 --> 00:15:52,569
It's "Young Master."

288
00:15:52,570 --> 00:15:53,770
Nonsense!

289
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:55,090
Its name is Xiaoyuan.

290
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:04,769
If you enjoy living alone,

291
00:16:04,770 --> 00:16:06,700
why did you hire four bodyguards?

292
00:16:08,810 --> 00:16:10,370
I won't make things hard for them.

293
00:16:11,020 --> 00:16:12,580
I only wanted these four to stay.

294
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,490
Don't tell me you hired them for me.

295
00:16:27,570 --> 00:16:28,890
Since when?

296
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:34,010
After what happened at Ji'an Apothecary.

297
00:16:34,530 --> 00:16:36,660
You really think that little of me?

298
00:16:42,900 --> 00:16:44,049
That was an accident.

299
00:16:44,050 --> 00:16:45,499
You know what an accident is?

300
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:46,169
Besides,

301
00:16:46,170 --> 00:16:48,219
I've gotten hurt way worse

302
00:16:48,220 --> 00:16:49,890
falling down or fighting crickets.

303
00:17:01,770 --> 00:17:03,540
Still thinking about that drink?

304
00:17:04,860 --> 00:17:06,620
First methamphetamine.

305
00:17:06,690 --> 00:17:07,480
Now radium.

306
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:10,180
The Japanese are treating China
like their testing ground for poison.

307
00:17:14,860 --> 00:17:16,620
I know what you're thinking.

308
00:17:17,340 --> 00:17:18,970
And I know what scares you.

309
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:20,770
You're afraid

310
00:17:21,300 --> 00:17:22,900
your mother's death

311
00:17:23,490 --> 00:17:25,899
was the same as

312
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:27,620
Secretary Xu's Fourth Madam's.

313
00:17:29,340 --> 00:17:30,770
Afraid?

314
00:17:31,340 --> 00:17:32,810
Wouldn't that be a good thing?

315
00:17:33,380 --> 00:17:34,730
I've been searching so long.

316
00:17:35,010 --> 00:17:36,720
I'm finally getting close to the truth.

317
00:17:38,140 --> 00:17:39,729
If this is the truth

318
00:17:39,730 --> 00:17:40,859
or if it's

319
00:17:40,860 --> 00:17:42,729
that close within reach,

320
00:17:42,730 --> 00:17:44,460
then who's been hiding it?

321
00:17:45,540 --> 00:17:46,900
You're afraid

322
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:49,460
what's behind it is even more terrifying
than the truth itself.

323
00:17:55,690 --> 00:17:56,570
Don't be.

324
00:17:57,730 --> 00:18:00,339
Whatever monsters are lurking out there,
once they're in my hands,

325
00:18:00,340 --> 00:18:02,010
they don't stand a chance.

326
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,570
Get some rest.

327
00:18:07,970 --> 00:18:10,290
You need to heal
before you can keep digging.

328
00:18:11,860 --> 00:18:12,770
Right.

329
00:18:13,380 --> 00:18:15,570
Your body's your greatest asset.

330
00:18:16,210 --> 00:18:17,290
What are you doing?

331
00:18:17,650 --> 00:18:18,620
Going to bed.

332
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:20,489
You sleep outside.

333
00:18:20,490 --> 00:18:21,900
I'm the patient.

334
00:18:23,730 --> 00:18:24,729
This is my house.

335
00:18:24,730 --> 00:18:25,970
You sleep on the floor.

336
00:18:27,560 --> 00:18:30,720
(End of Episode 27)

337
00:18:32,081 --> 00:18:33,721
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

338
00:18:33,721 --> 00:18:35,261
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

339
00:18:35,261 --> 00:18:36,511
♪However, the world changes♪

340
00:18:36,511 --> 00:18:38,431
♪You'll still be by my side♪

341
00:18:38,431 --> 00:18:40,121
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

342
00:18:40,121 --> 00:18:41,691
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

343
00:18:41,691 --> 00:18:43,261
♪If this is my final chapter♪

344
00:18:43,261 --> 00:18:45,761
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
